## entries() function

Returns an iterator of the own enumerable string keyed-value pairs.

**Signature:**

```typescript
declare function entries<T extends Record<Key, any>>(
  obj: T,
): Generator<Entries<T, keyof T>, void>;
```

## Example

```ts
[...entries({ a: 1, b: "2", c: true })];
// [["a", 1], ["b", "2"], ["c", true]]
```

see [fromEntries](https://fxts.dev/docs/fromEntries)
